      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "The Bitcoin Core dependencies for production builds are pegged and are unlikely to ever be using the latest versions of a 3rd party library.\r\n\r\nThe Visual Studio build is not used in production and is provided for developer convenience only. When doing a Visual Studio build on the Appveyor CI platform the dependencies, including libevent, are installed using Microsoft's vcpkg. The version is pegged by checking out a specific version of the vcpkg port files. Currently libevent is at `2.1.12`.\r\n\r\nWhich libevent version are you having a problem with and what's the warning or error you're getting?",
