      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I used \"pegged\" to mean the dependency is set at a specific version and not subject to any kind of automatic updating.\r\n\r\nThe idea with vcpkg is that if it's installed and in your path then the dependencies should all get installed automatically by `msbuild` (or more correctly `msbuild` automatically calling `vcpkg`).\r\n\r\nYou could try these steps:\r\n\r\n - Clone the vcpkg repo (sounds like you've already done this).\r\n - Build the vcpkg binaries using `bootstrap-vcpkg.bat`\r\n - Add the directory with vcpkg.exe to your path,\r\n - Change dir to the build_msvc directory in the bitcoin core source tree,\r\n - Run `vcpkg install --triplet x64-windows-static`\r\n - Run `msvc-autogen.py`\r\n - Run `msbuild /m bitcoin.sln /p:Platform=x64 /p:Configuration=Release /t:build`\r\n\r\nProper instructions are at https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/tree/master/build_msvc.",
